# Next.js app (`nextjs-simonask.io`)

## Stack

Next.js 16, React 19, Tailwind CSS 4 (`@import "tailwindcss"` in `globals.css`). Path alias `@/` → `src/`.

## Next.js 16 (not the version in training data)

APIs, conventions, and file structure may differ from your training data. Before writing Next code, read the relevant guide in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` and heed deprecation notices.

## Data

- Fetch via `sanityFetch()` in `src/sanity/load.ts` — do not call the Sanity client directly from pages
- GROQ queries live in `src/sanity/queries.ts`
- Preview/drafts: `getSanityClient()` uses preview when draft mode is on OR `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_ENV=staging` with `SANITY_API_READ_TOKEN`

## Layout shell

`layout.tsx` wraps pages with: `StagingBanner`, `SiteHeader`, `SiteFooter`, `StickyContact`, `ThemeProvider` + `ThemeScript`.

## Styling

- Semantic tokens in `globals.css` (`:root` / `html.dark`) — use Tailwind theme names: `background`, `foreground`, `muted`, `accent`, `border`, `surface`, `open-green`
- Article portable text: `ArticleBody` + `.article-*` classes in `globals.css`
- Prefer existing component patterns in `src/components/`

## API routes

- `api/draft-mode/enable|disable` — Studio Presentation preview
- `api/revalidate` — Sanity publish webhook (signed with `SANITY_REVALIDATE_SECRET`)

More detail: `memories/nextjs-conventions.md`
